post_text:
Why our admin LOVE EWA:
What I love about working at East Wake Academy is our endless effort to pursue excellence. I love being a part of a community of practitioners who do what's best for kids on a daily basis. Teachers are given the flexibility to shine in their area of expertise to meet the needs of each student who enters our buildings. Families are engaged in our school and support us wholeheartedly. I also enjoy the fact that parents make the CHOICE to bring their very best to our school and trust us to lay the foundation for their child's academia. We all like having the choice, right? #charterlove

post_text:
A message from Board Member and Parent:

As an EWA board member and EWA parent, I appreciate the community of our school. We have wonderful, caring, and focused teachers and administration that work hard every day to ensure that our kids are getting the best education and support possible. I love that we have a local board of EWA parents and members of our community that all have a vested personal interest in our school's success. Having a local school board that is dedicated just to our school is such a positive thing in my eyes. It is not located in another state or managing a vast number of schools as many other charter schools and school districts are, but right here with people who care.
#charterlove

post_text:
Another message from a parent:
EWA has been a second home for my kids for the past nine years. A home means that you are surrounded by people that love you and care deeply for your well-being. It is a place that they can grow and learn, taught by committed professionals who guide and challenge them along the way. EWA is that place where students are known as a person rather than just a GPA or a number on the back of an athletic uniform. Through established lines of communication from teachers and administrators, parents are more aware and involved in their child's education, which ultimately builds a sense of vibrant community. We are so fortunate that our family is a small part of the EWA family. #charterlove

More from our parents:
We love the quality education and communication of all the staff of EWA from top to bottom. Mr. Gay is often found at carpool opening doors and greeting us. He‚Äôs quick to respond to any concerns we have. Our children‚Äôs teachers are very communicative and work to resolve any issues they observe in our children. In a day and time where public school instruction gets a bad rap for poor test scores- EWA feels like a high dollar private school who treats its students as a family.
#charterlove

More LOVE from our parents:
We have been very lucky to have been a member of the EWA family for the past 6 years. From day one, we have been thankful for the teachers and staff. There is great joy knowing our children attend a school where the teachers and staff treat your children as one of their own. We have every confidence not only in the rigorous education they are receiving but also the love and compassion they need to grown into successful adults. #charterlove

post_text:
Why our parents love EWA:
East Wake Academy is more than just a charter school. It‚Äôs a family. A family filled with wonderful teachers and outstanding leadership. A place where kids feel safe and can thrive in their studies. EWA encourages students to achieve their goals and to keep pushing, never settling for anything less than their personal best. It‚Äôs hard to find this type of bond in a traditional school setting, but at EWA it‚Äôs a way of life. Having been a family of EWA for 15 years and counting, we can truly say there is no better school than East Wake Academy for our family. Go Eagles!!! #charterlove

If you are an essential worker or know of one connected to our EWA family or in our local community- PLEASE tag them and let us know! We would LOVE to see a picture of them in uniform or at work. We truly appreciate all of those on the frontlines as we all work together to get through the COVID-19 pandemic. If you follow us on Facebook, please comment on this post and give a SHOUT OUT to all the Super Heroes in our community-feel free to mention them by name! If you follow us on twitter please tweet @eastwakeacademy and show us pics of your local SuperHero. #weB4meEWA #weareallinthistogether

EAST WAKE ACADEMY will be closed on Friday 2/21/2020. With the current snowfall, worsening road conditions and forecast for low temperatures in the AM, we feel it is the safest option for our students, staff, and families! We hope this early announcement will allow our families to make the plans. NO MAKEUP PLANS HAVE BEEN MADE! So please do not speculate... just enjoy the first and hopefully only snow of the year!

Please be safe! Enjoy another long weekend and we will try it again on MONDAY!

post_text:
East Wake Academy's Lottery Application for the 2020 - 2021 school year ENDS on February 14th at noon. This applies to the Siblings of current students and the General Public.

Please go to www.eastwakeacademy.org and click on the Lottery Link on the Home page or the Admissions page. The lottery will take place on March 4th at 9:00 am in the Eagle Hall in the High School. You are welcome to attend, but it is not mandatory. You will receive an email within 45 minutes of the lottery letting you know whether you got in and what the next steps would be. If waitlisted, you will get an email letting you know what number you are on the waitlist. KEEP this email as you can check this for updates at any time. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact Kim Campbell at kcampbell@eastwakeacademy.org

post_text:
Families:

East Wake Academy is open and ready for business! We have power and smiling faces ready for your students. A number of our WINGS families said thanks for opening on time. We did not make an announcement this morning since we are opening at REGULAR time. With that said - remember what we ALWAYS say: Parents make the final decision for your family. If your family needs more time to get to school, take it! If you can not get out to get to school, that is ok as well - we will see you on Monday. We know some families do not have power, so if you can get to school - we do. You do what is right for your family.

Thank you so much for picking students up during our early release on Thursday. Our families did a great job and hope you were at home before the storm hit!

Important Announcement for Afternoon of Thursday 2/6/2020:

Due to the forecast for inclement weather tomorrow evening, we are going to end ALL after school activities at 5:00 pm on Thursday (2/6/2020). This is just precautionary and based on the forecast for tomorrow afternoon. We want to keep our EWA community safe. Thank you all for your understanding.

WINGS: Closing at 5:00 pm

Athletics: NO PRACTICE (coaches will also be reaching out)

Curriculum Night for Rising 9th graders has been moved to next Thursday, 2/13/2020 (info shared by the 8th-grade team)

All other campus activities ending by 5:00 pm
